commentTextItems.html: cover drive thru the diving fielder, that's 50, that's a win, that's 2 points, that's a half handy performance from bangladesh

commentPostTextItems.html: presentations. Aminul colecting the losing cheque: "I should congratulate out opening Mehrab Hossain... I'm very happy with the bowling and the fielding.... looking forward to the next match with Scotland"

$6000 for Lara: "getting our first win was important.... we conceded 25 wides, that's something we can't afford in the later matches.... it's good to see our team coming together, especially the batting"
and the man of the match is the unknown chap who goes by the name of Courtney Walsh
I'd transcribe something of what he says, but he's talking way too quickly in way too much of a monotone
and that's all we have from the land of Eire. Not the most exciting of matches and not themost unpredictable of results.

Tomorrow's matches are England v South Africa, and Sri Lanka v Zimbabwe. 2 very crucial matches. You'd expect the first to count as a Super 6 result, whilst the second could well decide which team enters the Super 6.
Zimbabwe of course relying on India's laughable appeal against the result of the Ind v Zim match being denied. A notion so ridiculous you have to think it's a hoax.
Until 945 GMT tomorrow, it's good evening from CI's Live Coverage Dept.
Until 945 GMT tomorrow, it's good evening from CI's Live Coverage Dept.

stretching forward with the most compact defence you'll see, and believe me, Chanders can be compact

commentTextItems.html: dabbed back to the bowler, indeed he's defending so Adams can get his half century, what a guy!
solid defence from Chanders, he's in no hurry
another formality shot, to the backward squar eleg
played around the corner to the short fine leg
pushed too far down the leg side, big pull shot from Adams, direct to the long leg fence
another full toss, drifting down the leg side, hoiked away for 4 over the forward square leg
